src.description: define a url or or a relative path on the local system to a file that should be transfered to a pdf

srcfile.description: define a absolute path to a file that should be transfered to a pdf

useragent.description: Text to put in the HTTP User-Agent request header field. Used to identify the request client software.

mimetype.description: mimetype of the source (when attribute src or srcfile are defined)

authpassword.description: Password sent to the target URL for Basic Authentication. Combined with username to form a base64 encoded string that is passed in the Authenticate header. Does not provide support for Integrated Windows, NTLM, or Kerebos authentication.

authuser.description: User name sent to the target URL for Basic Authentication. Combined with password to form a base64 encoded string that is passed in the Authenticate header. Does not provide support for Integrated Windows, NTLM, or Kerebos authentication.
